### [2 Kings (2 Samuel) Chapter 3](../../../bib/kjv/sa2003.htm#001.md)

[2 Kings (2 Samuel)](../../../bib/kjv/sa2001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">sa2 3:0</span></span>

Overview

[Sa2 3:1](../../../bib/kjv/sa2003.htm#001.md), During the war David still
waxes stronger; [Sa2 3:2](../../../bib/kjv/sa2003.htm#002.md), Six sons are
born to him in Hebron; [Sa2 3:6](../../../bib/kjv/sa2003.htm#006.md),
Abner, displeased with Ish-bosheth, [Sa2
3:7](../../../bib/kjv/sa2003.htm#007.md), revolts to David; [Sa2
3:13](../../../bib/kjv/sa2003.htm#013.md), David requires as a condition to
bring him his wife Michal; [Sa2 3:17](../../../bib/kjv/sa2003.htm#017.md),
Abner, having communed with the Israelites, is feasted by David, and
dismissed; [Sa2 3:22](../../../bib/kjv/sa2003.htm#022.md), Joab returning
from battle, is displeased with the king, and kills Abner; [Sa2
3:28](../../../bib/kjv/sa2003.htm#028.md), David curses Joab; [Sa2
3:31](../../../bib/kjv/sa2003.htm#031.md), and mourns for Abner.

